The paper discusses a novel technique for aggregate query processing in relational databases, specifically focusing on multi-way joins. This falls under the domain of database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also proposes a general framework for executing aggregation queries, which involves optimization techniques that can be categorized under distributed computing (cs.DC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG).
